.TH UNHINGED-TRANSCRIBE 1 "November 2025" "Unhinged" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
unhinged-transcribe \- Speech-to-text transcription for Unhinged platform

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B unhinged transcribe audio
\fIAUDIO_FILE\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B unhinged transcribe
command provides headless speech-to-text transcription using OpenAI Whisper.
Designed to be layered with GTK4 UI later, this command works standalone
for scripting and automation.

.SH SUBCOMMANDS

.SS AUDIO TRANSCRIPTION
.B unhinged transcribe audio
\fIAUDIO_FILE\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]

Transcribe audio file to text using Whisper model.

.B Supported Formats:
WAV, MP3, FLAC, OGG, M4A

.B Audio Transcription Options:
.RS
.TP
.B -m, --model \fIMODEL\fR
Whisper model size: tiny, base, small, medium, large (default: base)
.TP
.B -o, --output \fIPATH\fR
Save transcript to file (default: stdout)
.TP
.B --metadata
Include metadata (language, segments, duration)
.RE

.SH EXAMPLES

Transcribe audio file with default settings:
.RS
.B unhinged transcribe audio recording.wav
.RE

Transcribe with large model for better accuracy:
.RS
.B unhinged transcribe audio meeting.mp3 -m large
.RE

Save transcript to file:
.RS
.B unhinged transcribe audio speech.wav -o transcript.txt
.RE

Include metadata in output:
.RS
.B unhinged transcribe audio audio.wav --metadata
.RE

.SH OUTPUT

By default, transcript is printed to stdout. Use -o/--output to save to file.

With --metadata flag, output includes:
.RS
.TP
.B text
The transcribed text
.TP
.B language
Detected language code (e.g., "en", "es", "fr")
.TP
.B segments
Detailed segments with timestamps
.TP
.B duration
Estimated audio duration in seconds
.RE

.SH PERFORMANCE

.B Model Sizes and Performance:
.RS
.TP
.B tiny
~39M parameters, fastest, lower accuracy
.TP
.B base
~74M parameters, good balance (default)
.TP
.B small
~244M parameters, better accuracy
.TP
.B medium
~769M parameters, high accuracy
.TP
.B large
~1550M parameters, highest accuracy, slowest
.RE

.B Memory Requirements:
.RS
.TP
tiny: ~1GB VRAM
.TP
base: ~2GB VRAM
.TP
small: ~3GB VRAM
.TP
medium: ~5GB VRAM
.TP
large: ~10GB VRAM
.RE

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES

.TP
.B CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES
Specify which GPU to use (e.g., "0" for first GPU)

